                                            <li>Events auto-deactivate after their Time Out window expires.</li>
                                            <li>Use the <strong>Semester</strong> and <strong>Academic Year</strong> fields for proper sanctions tracking.</li>
                                        </ul>
                                    </div>

                                    <div style="background: #f0fff4; border-radius: 12px; padding: 20px; border-left: 4px solid #38a169;">
                                        <h4 style="margin: 0 0 8px 0; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;">
                                            <img src="images/logo.png" alt="Logo" style="height: 32px; width: auto;" />
                                            INFOTECH Student Enrollment
                                        </h4>
                                        <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 20px; color: var(--neutral-600); line-height: 1.8;">
                                            <li>Navigate to <strong>Enroll</strong> from the sidebar to register new students.</li>
                                            <li>Each student requires <strong>5 fingerprint samples</strong> for verification.</li>
                                            <li>Students imported via PDF are <strong>unverified</strong> until they complete fingerprint enrollment.</li>
                                            <li>Use Student ID format: <strong>YYYY-XXXX-L</strong> (e.g., 2024-0001-A).</li>
                                            <li>To recapture a student's fingerprints, use the recapture button on the <strong>Students</strong> tab.</li>
                                        </ul>
                                    </div>

                                    <div style="background: #fffbeb; border-radius: 12px; padding: 20px; border-left: 4px solid #d69e2e;">
                                        <h4 style="margin: 0 0 8px 0;">📊 Attendance & Records</h4>
                                        <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 20px; color: var(--neutral-600); line-height: 1.8;">
                                            <li>Students scan their fingerprint on the <strong>Attendance</strong> page to Time In / Time Out.</li>
                                            <li>View records on the <strong>Records</strong> tab, filtered by event.</li>
                                            <li>Export records to <strong>Excel</strong> or <strong>PDF</strong> using the export buttons.</li>
                                            <li>Deleted records are <strong>soft-deleted</strong> and retained for audit purposes.</li>
                                        </ul>
                                    </div>

                                    <div style="background: #fff5f5; border-radius: 12px; padding: 20px; border-left: 4px solid #e53e3e;">
                                        <h4 style="margin: 0 0 8px 0;">⚖️ Sanctions</h4>
                                        <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 20px; color: var(--neutral-600); line-height: 1.8;">
                                            <li>Configure sanction rules under <strong>Settings → Sanction Rules</strong>.</li>
                                            <li>Rules are defined per semester and absence count.</li>
                                            <li>Use <strong>"or more"</strong> for the highest tier (e.g., 4 or more absences).</li>
                                            <li>View a student's sanctions from the <strong>Students</strong> tab sanction icon.</li>
                                        </ul>
                                    </div>

                                    <div style="background: #ebf8ff; border-radius: 12px; padding: 20px; border-left: 4px solid #3182ce;">
                                        <h4 style="margin: 0 0 8px 0;">💾 Database & Backups</h4>
                                        <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 20px; color: var(--neutral-600); line-height: 1.8;">
                                            <li><strong>Export JSON</strong> creates a full backup of students, events, and records.</li>
                                            <li><strong>Import JSON</strong> restores from a backup (overwrites current data).</li>
                                            <li><strong>Import PDF</strong> adds students from a PDF student list (unverified).</li>
                                            <li><strong>Reset Database</strong> clears all data except admin accounts for a new school year.</li>
                                        </ul>
                                    </div>

                                    <div style="background: #faf5ff; border-radius: 12px; padding: 20px; border-left: 4px solid #805ad5;">
                                        <h4 style="margin: 0 0 8px 0;">🛡️ Admin Accounts & Security</h4>
                                        <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 20px; color: var(--neutral-600); line-height: 1.8;">
                                            <li>Maximum of <strong>5 admin accounts</strong> allowed.</li>
                                            <li>Admins can only <strong>delete their own account</strong>.</li>
                                            <li>Set a <strong>security question</strong> when creating accounts for password recovery.</li>
                                            <li>Use <strong>"Forgot Password?"</strong> on the login page to self-reset via your security question.</li>
                                            <li>Change your password under <strong>Settings → My Profile</strong>.</li>
                                            <li>All admin actions are recorded in <strong>Activity Logs</strong>.</li>
                                        </ul>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        }
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        }
    </div>
</div>

@if (showFormatVisualizer)
{
    <div class="modal-overlay" @onclick="CloseFormatVisualizer"></div>
    <div class="modal-card" style="max-width: 800px; z-index: 1001; position: fixed; top: 50%; left: 50%; transform: translate(-50%, -50%); background: white; padding: 24px; border-radius: 12px; box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.15); max-height: 90vh; overflow-y: auto;">
        <div class="modal-header" style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; margin-bottom: 16px;">
            <h3 style="margin: 0;">@(isExcelFormat ? "Excel Database Import Format" : "PDF Student Import Format")</h3>
            <button class="btn-close" @onclick="CloseFormatVisualizer" style="background: none; border: none; font-size: 1.5rem; cursor: pointer;">&times;</button>
        </div>
        <div class="modal-body">
            @if (isExcelFormat)
            {
                <p>The Excel file must contain four sheets: <strong>Students</strong>, <strong>Events</strong>, <strong>Attendance</strong>, and <strong>Logs</strong>. The first row of each sheet must be the headers.</p>
                <p><strong>Students Sheet Columns:</strong></p>
                <div style="overflow-x: auto;">
                    <table class="table" style="font-size: 0.9em; min-width: 600px;">
                        <thead>
                            <tr style="background: var(--neutral-50);">
                                <th style="padding: 8px;">Id</th>
                                <th style="padding: 8px;">StudentId</th>
                                <th style="padding: 8px;">Name</th>
                                <th style="padding: 8px;">Email</th>
                                <th style="padding: 8px;">Program</th>
                                <th style="padding: 8px;">YearLevel</th>
                                <th style="padding: 8px;">EnrolledDate</th>
                                <th style="padding: 8px;">IsActive</th>
                                <th style="padding: 8px;">Section</th>
                                <th style="padding: 8px;">IsVerified</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <td style="padding: 8px; border-top: 1px solid var(--neutral-200);">1</td>
                                <td style="padding: 8px; border-top: 1px solid var(--neutral-200);">2023-001</td>
                                <td style="padding: 8px; border-top: 1px solid var(--neutral-200);">John Doe</td>
                                <td style="padding: 8px; border-top: 1px solid var(--neutral-200);">john@example.com</td>
                                <td style="padding: 8px; border-top: 1px solid var(--neutral-200);">BSIT</td>
                                <td style="padding: 8px; border-top: 1px solid var(--neutral-200);">1</td>
                                <td style="padding: 8px; border-top: 1px solid var(--neutral-200);">2023-08-01</td>
                                <td style="padding: 8px; border-top: 1px solid var(--neutral-200);">TRUE</td>
                                <td style="padding: 8px; border-top: 1px solid var(--neutral-200);">A</td>
                                <td style="padding: 8px; border-top: 1px solid var(--neutral-200);">FALSE</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>
                <p class="text-muted" style="font-size: 0.8em; margin-top: 16px; color: var(--neutral-500);">Note: You can generate a template by exporting the current database.</p>
            }
            else
            {
                <p>The PDF file should be a list of students containing their ID, Name, Program, and Year Level. The importer looks for lines that start with a student ID pattern (e.g., Year-Number or letters followed by numbers).</p>
                <div style="background: var(--neutral-50); padding: 16px; border-radius: 8px; border: 1px dashed var(--neutral-300); font-family: monospace;">
                    <p style="margin: 0; color: var(--neutral-500);">Example PDF Content:</p>
                    <br/>
                    <p style="margin: 0;">Student List - BSIT 2023</p>
                    <p style="margin: 0;">-----------------------</p>
                    <p style="margin: 0; font-weight: bold; color: var(--neutral-900);">2023-0001 Smith, John A. BSIT 1</p>
                    <p style="margin: 0; font-weight: bold; color: var(--neutral-900);">2023-0002 Doe, Jane B. BSCS 2</p>
                    <p style="margin: 0; font-weight: bold; color: var(--neutral-900);">2023-0003 Johnson, Bob C. BSIS 3</p>
                    <br/>
                    <p style="margin: 0; color: var(--neutral-500);">The importer will extract the ID, name, program, and year level from lines matching this pattern.</p>
                </div>
            }
        </div>
        <div class="modal-footer" style="margin-top: 24px; text-align: right;">
            <button class="btn btn-primary" @onclick="CloseFormatVisualizer">Close</button>
        </div>
    </div>
}

@if (showConfirmationModal)
{
    <div class="modal-overlay">
        <div class="modal-card confirmation-card">
            <div class="modal-body">
                <div class="confirmation-icon">⚠️</div>
                <h3>Are you sure?</h3>
                <p>@confirmationMessage</p>
                <div class="confirmation-actions">
                    <button class="btn btn-cancel" @onclick="CancelConfirmation">No, Cancel</button>
                    <button class="btn btn-danger" @onclick="ProceedWithConfirmation">Yes, Proceed</button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
}
}

